SOME IS NINE broke a step slow, quickly recovered and moved up widest then cleared in hand into the first turn, dropped in and set a rated pace towards the inside, handled the initial bid of the winner near the furlong grounds, spurted back clear, kept on gamely but wasn't quite good enough through the final yards. CAGED PIXIE showed speed then was rated back off the leader while saving ground, moved up to have aim past the wire the first time, saw the leaders get away leaving the far turn, chased and went evenly late. MISS WILD , three wide early, moved up to take aim nearing the half mile marker, gave chase two wide around the final turn then faded through the final sixteenth. EMMA AND I lagged back, was taken four wide for the backstretch run and failed to respond. LIFE IN FLASH , in range early while saving some ground, failed to go on under pressure past the three eighths and retreated. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAMA G'S WISH rated in the clear and off of a hotly contested pace, eagerly made her way forward past the three eighths, eased out leaving the far turn and took aim behind foes, shifted four wide while put to pressure into the lane, closed determinedly under a drive, took command late and went clear at the wire. VIOLENT VIXEN , attended the pace three deep and under nice rating, moved to the attack leaving the far turn, responded when roused and kicked clear into the lane, drifted in on her left lead near the sixteenth pole, switched over to her correct lead soon after and gave way grudgingly. OUR LIBERTY BELLE , off a contested pace and off the inside, was under pressure past the quarter pole, angled four wide for the drive and closed steadily. PARISH BELLE , bumped leaving the gate, battled between runners past the wire the first turn, emerged in a battle outside NOBLE BID soon into the backstretch, gained a slim lead nearing the far turn, could not resist VIOLENT VIXEN's bid past the three sixteenths then weakened through the drive. CANOODLE , bumped and in tight at the break, saved ground off the pace and lacked a rally. NOBLE BID came out a bit at the break tightening a rival, corrected and disputed the pace inside a pair of foes heading to the first turn, held a tenuous advantage dueling inside PARISH BELLE past the three eighths, ceded the lead into the far turn, failed to go on past the three sixteenths and faltered.
